        "title": "feat(channels): shared progress-lane engine — unify per-channel progress streaming",
        "body": "Reopens the work auto-closed in #88337. **This is not a duplicate of #85200** — and ClawSweeper's own close review says so:\n\n> \"Current main does not already implement the shared progress-lane SDK\"\n\n#85200 (merged) adds **Discord-only** assistant commentary in progress drafts. This PR is the **channel-agnostic engine** that *absorbs* that behavior and #87072 (Telegram interleaved lane) into one shared `openclaw/plugin-sdk/progress-lane`, so every channel (Discord, MSTeams, Feishu, lmstudio, Telegram) drives the same controller through a thin per-channel sink. That is the shared approach @obviyus explicitly asked for — it is the *superset* of #85200, not a copy of it. The auto-close conflated \"the Discord feature is merged\" with \"the shared engine is superseded\"; the bot itself tagged this `needs-human` and then applied the close anyway.\n\n## State (branch `feat/shared-progress-lane`, all green)\n- `e6ba2125d3a` — functional engine: `transcript.ts` (channel-neutral body math) + `controller.ts` (`createProgressLane`) + `sink.ts` (`ProgressLaneSink`/`ProgressLaneConfig`), with 9 passing tests.\n- `75efabee1c2` — registered as the `openclaw/plugin-sdk/progress-lane` export (manifest + flat re-export; `plugin-sdk:check-exports` + `tsgo:core` clean).\n\n## Next (channel sinks — each a thin adapter, no LCD)\n1. Discord sink over `createDiscordDraftStream` (`spill()`→`forceNewMessage()`), wired into `message-handler.process.ts`.\n2. MSTeams (`reply-stream-controller`), Feishu (`streaming-card`), lmstudio.\n3. Telegram cutover last (faithful extraction of its own logic onto the shared controller), after #87072 merges.\n\n## Open maintainer calls\n- Config namespace (`streaming.progress.*`?) and sequencing vs #87072.\n\n@obviyus @bryanpearson — keeping this open as a draft for the shared-engine decision; please don't auto-supersede against #85200.\n",
